snippet.textDisplay: pretty impressive i'm sure if you used a pattern and just altered it to your idea that it would work much better especially the jacket sleeves. if you go without a pattern make each piece with like 1/4 to 1/2 inch of extra fabric when you form fit to allow for sewing pieces together and still have room to comfortably slip it on and be able to move in. also if you don't use a pattern you should cut all the pieces and make sure they are the same size and shape for both arms or legs before sewing them, so when you do sew them they will be more even when everything comes together. i'm sure you figured out things that you could've done that would have made it easier and come out looking better, but overall you really did an amazing job for a 1st time sewer and trying to free hand your pattern pieces. i say 9.5 for your the actual wearability and the look and the effort. tbh, i like to sew and i have sewn a lot, tho i usually hand sew cuz i don't have my own machine, but i have used one before, and i'm not sure i could have done any better or even as well. so good job! i'm interested to see your 2nd attempt at this outfit, after learning a few things from your 1st try, and see how much better you can do and how it will look on the 2nd try.

snippet.textDisplay: In my experience, anytime I’ve had to plead with someone (event planners to caterers to lawyers) to get an appointment, and then pay them exorbitant fees to take my business, it hasn’t worked out well. People like that often have such huge egos they don’t listen to their clients. They seem less interested in meeting the clients’ needs and wants, and more interested in their own vision or; in some cases, more focused on other clients they deem to be more important. In situations like that, I’ve been made to feel like an after thought at best and an inconvenience at worst, despite the fact that I was paying as much or more for their services. I’m sure Ryland can find an excellent seamstress or tailor who will be excited to work with him and make his dream wedding designs a reality.
